# Start-Task Development Principles

This rule defines the development principles and process specifications that must be followed when executing development under the `start-task` command.

## Related Rules

- **Operation mode rule**: [operation-modes.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/operator/start-task/operation-modes.mdc) - Defines four operation modes (Cautious, Multi-Task, Fast, Default)
- **Jira check rule**: [start-task-jira-check.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/operator/start-task/start-task-jira-check.mdc) - Defines Jira ticket check principles

## Applicable Scenarios

This rule applies to all development phases during `start-task` command execution, including:
- **Operation mode selection** (new)
- Development plan confirmation and execution
- Code modification and implementation
- Report generation after development is complete
- Confirmation flow before commit
- MR creation and report attachment

---

## 🚨 Impact of Operation Mode on Development Principles

**CRITICAL**: Different operation modes affect how development principles are executed. Behavior must be adjusted according to the chosen mode.

### Mode Comparison Table

| Principle | Cautious mode | Multi-task mode | Fast mode | Default mode |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| **Confirmation flow** | Confirm each step | Only plan confirmation | Only schedule confirmation | Confirm each phase |
| **Development report** | Detailed + rollback plan | Summary per phase | Simplified (batch summary) | Standard |
| **Commit timing** | Single commit | Per phase | Per task | Single commit |
| **MR strategy** | Single + detailed description | Unified + link all ticket numbers | Independent per task | Single |
| **Interruption handling** | Stop immediately | Pause current phase | Stop and let user choose (skip/pause/cancel) | Wait for confirmation |

### Mode-specific Principles

#### Cautious mode additional requirements
- Must show impact scope before each code modification
- MR Description must include rollback plan
- Prohibit any "while-we're-at-it optimizations"

#### Multi-task mode additional requirements
- Git notes must record current phase progress
- Auto-commit after each phase completes (no waiting for confirmation)
- MR Description must link all sub-task ticket numbers
- **Must follow Multi-Task Mode SOP**: Includes full sub-task reading and scheduling (only schedule sub-tasks with AI instructions), Requirement ticket as feature branch, Sub-task ticket as commit scope, check/fill Original Estimate and switch to "In Progress" before starting, switch to Development Review and leave a phase report to notify RD after completion, auto-advance to next sub-task after completing one, and follow the start-task MR specification flow after all scheduled tasks complete.
- **Scheduling scope restriction (new)**: In Multi-Task mode, each run only inventories/schedules Sub-tasks that are **in To Do status** and **contain AI instructions**; other sub-tasks are not included in this automatic scheduling.

See:
- [multi-task-mode-sop.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/operator/start-task/multi-task-mode-sop.mdc)

#### Fast mode additional requirements
- Confirm the "schedule list" with the user before starting (authorization point)
- Development plan not shown to user (executed internally)
- Provide skip/pause/cancel options when errors occur
- Send system notification only after all tasks complete

For detailed specifications, see: [operation-modes.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/operator/start-task/operation-modes.mdc)

