### Save Command

Use the `.cursor/scripts/operator/save-start-task-info.mjs` script to save:

```bash
# Method 1: Use individual parameters to save start task plan
node .cursor/scripts/operator/save-start-task-info.mjs \
  --ticket=IN-107113 \
  --summary="[title]" \
  --type=Bug \
  --status="To Do" \
  --assignee="FE-William" \
  --priority="Medium" \
  --steps='["step 1", "step 2", "step 3"]' \
  --source-branch=main \
  --ai-completed=true \

# Verify save succeeded
node .cursor/scripts/operator/save-start-task-info.mjs --verify

# Read existing notes
node .cursor/scripts/operator/save-start-task-info.mjs --read

# Update existing notes (merge mode)
node .cursor/scripts/operator/save-start-task-info.mjs --update --steps='["new step"]'

```

### Mandatory Checkpoints

At the following times, the AI **MUST** confirm Git notes have been saved:

- [ ] **After user confirms development plan (Fast mode: after user confirms schedule list)** → Immediately execute `save-start-task-info.mjs`
- [ ] **Execute `--verify` validation** → Confirm save succeeded
- [ ] **Before preparing to commit after development** → Check notes exist
- [ ] **Before executing `cr` command** → Verify notes exist again

### Handling Missing Notes

If Git notes are found missing when committing or creating an MR:

1. **Stop immediately** the flow
2. **Ask the user** whether to supplement the development plan
3. Use script to save:
   ```bash
   node .cursor/scripts/operator/save-start-task-info.mjs \
     --ticket={extracted from branch name} \
     --summary="[supplemental title]" \
     --type={inferred type} \
     --steps='["completed steps"]' \
     --ai-completed=true
   ```
4. **Continue flow only after verifying save succeeded**

### Process Checklist

```
## Phase 0: Mode Selection (new)
- [ ] 🚨 Display operation mode options to user
- [ ] Identify user's chosen mode
- [ ] Record mode for subsequent flow

## Phase 1: Initialization
- [ ] Read Jira ticket info
- [ ] Check RD suggestions (for AI markers)
- [ ] Analyze requirements and formulate development plan
- [ ] 🚨 Decide whether to show plan based on mode

## Phase 2: Confirm Plan
- [ ] Show development plan to user (Fast mode: skip)
- [ ] Wait for user confirmation (Fast mode: skip)
- [ ] 🚨 Save development plan to Git notes (including operationMode) ← easy to omit
- [ ] 🚨 Verify save succeeded

## Phase 3: Development Execution
- [ ] Execute development steps
- [ ] Complete code modifications
- [ ] 🚨 Cautious mode: confirm each step
- [ ] 🚨 Multi-task mode: independent commit per phase

## Phase 4: Completion Report
- [ ] Generate development report (based on Jira type)
- [ ] Show report to user for confirmation (Fast mode: skip)
- [ ] Update Git notes (if report exists)

## Phase 5: Submit MR
- [ ] 🚨 Check Git notes exist
- [ ] Execute commit (Multi-task mode: already done)
- [ ] Create MR (auto-reads notes to generate description)
- [ ] 🚨 Multi-task mode: MR links all sub-task ticket numbers
- [ ] 🚨 Fast mode: independent MR per task

## Phase 6: Notification (new)
- [ ] 🚨 Fast mode: send system notification after all tasks complete
- [ ] Multi-task mode: send system notification after all tasks complete
```

