## MR Report Attachment Rules

**CRITICAL**: After the user confirms the development report, the report content must be attached to the MR description.

### Attachment Format

The report should be added to the MR description in Markdown format, structured as follows:

```markdown
## 🎯 Development Plan

This MR was initiated by the `start-task` command. Below is the development plan:

- [Step 1]
- [Step 2]
...

## 📋 Related Ticket Info

| Item | Value |
|---|---|
| **Ticket** | [TICKET](URL) |
| **Title** | [SUMMARY] |
| **Type** | [ISSUE_TYPE] |

---

## 📊 Development Report

[Report content based on Jira card type]
```

**Notes**:
- Development plan and related ticket info are independent sections
- Related ticket info only includes ticket number (with hyperlink), title, and type
- Development report is an optional section, generated based on Jira card type

### Implementation Location

Development report updating and attachment is handled by the `.cursor/scripts/operator/update-development-report.mjs` script:

**Script functions**:
- Read and update `startTaskInfo` in Git notes
- Save development report to the `developmentReport` field
- Generate formatted MR description (using table format to avoid line break issues)

**Usage**:

```bash
# Update development report (provide content directly)
node .cursor/scripts/operator/update-development-report.mjs --report="<report-content>"

# Read report content from file
node .cursor/scripts/operator/update-development-report.mjs --report-file="<path-to-report-file>"

# Read current startTaskInfo
node .cursor/scripts/operator/update-development-report.mjs --read

# Output formatted MR description (Markdown format)
node .cursor/scripts/operator/update-development-report.mjs --format
```

**AI flow usage**:

1. After the AI generates the development report, use `--report` parameter to save report content to Git notes
2. When executing `cr single-ticket`, use `--format` to get the formatted MR description
3. Pass the formatted description to the MR creation flow

